</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,970,1370]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1269,1295]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
Due to the quadrate condition of the head, the weak tooth on the ventral margin of the mandible, the fact that one species has dentate hind coxae, and similarities in genitalia, this species-group is likely most closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[497,606,1344,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthlama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blakeii">
<emphasis box="[497,606,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">S. blakeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[663,806,1344,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cexyoides">
<emphasis box="[663,806,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">S. cexyoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
